Until the date of his appointment, Maleiane held the position of Minister of Economy and Finance, a post to which Nyusi nominated Ernesto Max Elias Tonela. With these appointments, Carlos Agostinho do Rosário, João Osvaldo Machatine, Augusta Maíta and Carlos Silyia were left out of the chessboard of Nyusi's executive. Former Minister of Mineral Resources and Energy, Ernesto Max Elias Tonela, was appointed  Minister of Economy and Finance. He replaces Maleiane. Former Minister of Trade and Commerce, Carlos Alberto Fortes Mesquita, has been appointed to the post of Minister of Public Works, Housing and Water Resources, replacing Joao Osvaldo Machatine. Former Deputy Minister of Health, Lídia da Graça Cardoso, was appointed Minister of the Sea, Inland Waters and Fisheries. She replaces Augusta Maíta. Former Chairperson of the National Petroleum Institute, Carlos Joaquim Zacarias, was appointed Minister of Mineral Resources and Energy. He replaces Tonela. Silvino Augusto José Moreno was appointed Minister of Industry and Commerce. He replaces Carlos Mesquita. Amílcar Paia Tivane has been appointed Deputy Minister of Economy. No new Deputy Minister of Health to replace the vacancy left by the now Minister of the Sea, Inland Waters and Fisheries Lidia Cardoso  had been appointed yet. --ChannelAfrica-- 